This is my first pregnancy where I have been able to support my body, using essential oils.

When I was pregnant with Isla and Eadie, I made sure I had Panadol on hand, Mylanta in the fridge, and I was having physical treatment for my aching body every 2-3 weeks.

Pregnancy this time around has been COMPLETELY different.

I have taken Panadol once (thanks Peppermint and Frankincense), I don‚Äôt even have Mylanta in the fridge (DigestZen to the rescue!) and my aching muscles have been soothed with AromaTouch, Frankincense it Ice Blue. 

Not to mention being able to support my emotional wellbeing (... those pregnancy hormones ü§î) with a range of oils that I diffuse daily (Balance, anyone?).

Next stop... make up my labour oils bundle.

üìÖ 35 weeks and counting.

