nt for frogs and watch the buzzy bees do their work. 
‚Ä¢

My babies are happy. They show gratitude, resiliency, and reciprocity. They love deeply and trust openly. They sleep soundly at night after days of laughter, sunshine, and adventures. 
‚Ä¢

I don‚Äôt hover over my babies. I let them get dirty. If they fall down I let them get up. If they‚Äôre bored I encourage them to go outside to find inspiration. 
‚Ä¢

I know I‚Äôm different. I can see and feel the discomfort in some as I give my babies the space to explore their relationship with the land. I have moments where I question my instincts and how I parent. 
‚Ä¢

